review_blob: Blonde beer with nice cap rich of flavour recalling honey. Amazing taste with an unbelivable balance between sweet and bitter. You cant distinguish between since its balancing its amazing. Really nice body not loosing its really easy drinkable characteristic. Amazing!

vivid gold beer with persistent and compact foam, you can feel citrus and spicy in its aroma. its complex taste starts dry, continue with bitter and finish with sour and citrus. unbelivable evolution of taste and a nice body make this beer awesome!
White and light beer, not a great body, really drinkable with a pleased light apple taste in aftertaste.
Dark beer with dark cups,Dark chocolate and soia sauce ib the nose. Aroma it is purely chocolate with a thin toasted malt aftertaste. Great body for this great beer! AMAZING!
beer_name: BrewDog / Ngne  / Mikkeller Black Tokyo* Horizon

review_blob: Golden beer with really thin foam and no gas. Lemon and citrix at the nose with mold notes its aroma. Young wood and and lemon in mouth with really nice sour taste in the end.

Aroma is coffee with chocolate notes and also foam have coffee aroma. Black beer with nice foam and the taste is coffee persistant. The final is dark chocolate with a little bitter that remain at the palate. Nice stout really drinkable due to its 4%

Citrus wort and spicy in the nose with an intense aroma. At the apparence ambered beer with nice foam. Drinking it is sweet with fruity notes that become sour in the end (tannic). Its a pleasure drinking this beer and the sweet ots perfectly balanced by its sour characteristic. Nice beer!

Citrus and acetic notes in its aroma. This IPA have colour like a keller beer and nice foam (draft). When you drink it you can feel bitter taste and grapefruit really persistant. In the end sour notes are really pleased drinking this beer. Nice to drink amd overall nice beer, if you like sour beers this is your IPA

Fruits like citrus in its aroma. This ambered IPA have nice dolour but not a great foam (bottled). When you drink it you can feel bitter taste from ipa more persistant than fruits aroma that you can feel. This IPA it is easy to drink and you dont feel its 7%
Nice amora of fruits, at the apparence intense blonde with nice foam. Bitter is persistant and its nice body with fruity notes its a pleasure. Bitter is persistant for an extream beer!

Chocolate and toasted malt in its aroma, black beer with a great body and persistent foam. Taste is chocolare licorice and coffee for a great porter. Not persistant in the palate nice taste and a nice porter!
beer_name: The Brewery Britomart Eight Ball Porter

review_blob: Dark beer with light foam. Aroma is chestnut, smoked, and notes of cigars. Taste is alchool at the beginning with winy notes nuts and woods all coming from barrell wood aging.

(Year: 2011) dark brown without foam. Aroma with wood, wine and you can feel notes of blue cheese and vinegard. Drinking it: toasted malt, chocolate and a bit of sour at the end. It can recall a stout beer eaged in wine wood barrells.

(Year 2009) dark red with no foam. Aroma has cerry notes and wood is present in the nose (it comes from cerry pit). Aged in steel barrels coming from low fermentation beer. Drinking it you can feel fruits and vanilla while it leave a persistant sour taste at the end.

At the apparence gold beer with really light foam. Mix of flavours at the nose while its sour taste it is persistant with citric notes. This is a great belgian gueuze in which the sour taste is the greater one, nice to drink also during lunch. Cantillon is always a warranty.

At the apparence red rubin with thin foam. Its aroma is hoppy with not so more fruits. Drinking it it is like an IPA but less bitter even if bitter taste and notes of fruits characterize its really nice body.

Hop and fruits (like passion fruit and raspberry) in its aroma. The IPA style of this IPA its perfectly balanced from an accurate hop selection coming from pacific ocean. When you drink it you can feel bitter taste from ipa without leaving space for fruits and malr flavours. This pacific IPA can be drink by everyone even if you dont like IPA. Unique taste for a unique beer.

Ananas tropical fruits and a bit spicy in background in its aroma. In apparece white beer and also smelling it seems like a blanche. Once you drink it will be completely diffrrent and its dry hopping brewery make this beer really bitter and dry. Easy to drink and really refreshing and thirst-quenching.

In apparence blonde beer with nice compact foam. Its aroma it is light recalling the malt tipical of lager german beers. The taste of this beer it is delicate with spicy notes in background. Those spicy flavours are more persistant in the bottled version of this beer. As a whole nice beer without complex taste and really easy to drink.

At the apparence this beer is light red with really light foam tipic of those beers. Its aroma recall wood and citrus and its sour taste it is persistant. You can feel the add of fresh hop drinking it at the end leaving a bit of bitter on the palate. This is a great sour beligan beer with which Cantillon perfectly mix old and fresh hop for a unique taste beer.

At the apparence this beer is like a bockbier with really light foam. This is an italian sour beer. Its sour taste it is light and obtained from cherry fruits that call back fruity flavours drinking it. This beer is more easy to drink compared with belgian goeses. Persistant on the palate and a bit sour spicy at the end. It is the right one if you want start drink and discover those kinds of beers. Approved by Kuaska

In apparence dark beer with not so more persistent foam. Alcohol and licorice are the most powerful tastes at first drink. It is really hoppy and this make its IPA taste dominant compared to the stout beersone. As a whole persistant body complex taste but probably too much alcohol ( dont know if this is due to the fact that I try it bottled)
